In this section, "extraordinary dividend" or "extraordinary distribution" includes any dividend or distribution of cash or other property with a fair market value, that when combined with the fair market value of any other dividends or distributions made in the preceding 12 months exceeds the lesser of:
10% of the insurer's surplus as regards policyholders as of December 31 of the preceding year; or
for a life insurer, the net gain from operations of the insurer not including:
for an insurer that is not a life insurer, the net investment income of the insurer not including:
